[The new ASF outbreak, on a farm in the Kaiserstuhl district of Emmendingen, Baden-Wuerttemberg, has been notified by Germany to the OIE on Thu 26 May 2022. Date of start - 24 May 2022; date of confirmation - 25 May 2022.

Diagnosis obtained by PCR at the Friedrich-Loeffler Institute on 26 May 2022
Affected population:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered or killed for commercial use / Vaccinated
Swine / 35 / 16 / 16 / 19 / 0 / 0

The report, including a map, is available at https://wahis.oie.int/#/report-info?reportId=54607.

Baden-Wuerttemberg is a state in southwest Germany bordering France and Switzerland. The Black Forest lies in its mountainous southwest. The leap of ASF, probably from northeast Germany, to this region is bad news to the local pig industry and a serious threat to the French and Swiss pig industries. Results of the epidemiological investigation into the source and route of introduction are anticipated with interest. - Mod.AS

